fields.label_info_text: If LMP is unknown and ultrasound wasn't done or it wasn't done early (before 24 weeks), then assess GA based on Symphysis Fundal Height (SFH) or abdominal palpation. Compare this GA against ultrasound GA (if done).
fields.label_info_title: GA from SFH or abdominal palpation - weeks

v_numeric_integer.err: Enter a Valid GA from SFH or abdominal palpation - weeks value

v_min.err: GA from SFH or abdominal palpation - weeks should 4 or greater

v_max.err: GA from SFH or abdominal palpation - weeks should be 40 or less

fields.label_info_text: If the difference between GA from LMP and early ultrasound is one week or less, then use GA from LMP. If the difference is more than 7 days, use the early ultrasound GA. If ultrasound was done late, use GA from LMP. Between late ultrasound and SFH or abdominal palpation, use your best judgment to select GA.
